xterm -ti vt52 -tn vt52

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/VT52#Escape_sequences
echo -e '\x1bHXXX'


how to put X to top right corner:

	>>> chr(32)
	' '

	$ echo -e '\x1bY  X'

auto-detect terminal:

	echo -e '\x1b[6n\x1bZ'
		\x1b[6n (DSR) causes ANSI terminals to respond with ESC[<row>;<col>R
		\x1bZ causes VT52 terminals to respond with ESC/{K,L,Z}
